  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Marginalized Groups Livelihood and Values-Based Holistic Community Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Improving Marginalized Groups Livelihoods and Values-Based Holistic Community Development project will be implemented in partnership with four new partners: Chetthor, Por Thom Elderly Association, Association of Farmer Development and Khmer Women&#x2019;s Cooperation for Development. The project will affect 620 families in four communities located in the Prey Veng, Svay Rieng, and Kompot provinces. These families will divide in to 32 self-help groups, and four youth groups. Heifer will provide pigs and sows to 150 families, goats to 35 families, poultry to 375 families, and fingerlings fish and poultry to another 60 families. Each family will also receive agricultural support such as fodder and forage seeds, saplings and vegetable seeds for home gardening. Project participants will receive training on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, self-help group management and leadership, improved animal management, home gardening and organic farming, HIV/AIDS, among others. In addition, 1056 project participants will receive Values-Based Literacy Education. Another 1,240 families will benefit through Passing on the Gift. The project also aims to select and train 8 village animal health workers who will provide animal services to their communities</narrative>
  </description>
